        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-22T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-22T23:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Jessup, Philip C./8–2349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-23T00:00:00-04:00">August 23, 1949—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1008. Pls transmit fol message to Romulo from Jessup: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I have only just now recd your ltr of Aug 9, 1949 concerning the
                            proposed Southeast Asian Assoc. I had previously recd the telegraphic
                            msg which you were kind enough to send to Butterworth and me through the
                            Amer Emb in Manila. You will by now I am sure have recd our reply which
                            I believe answers questions and suggestions made in your ltr to me.</p>
                        <p>All I can add at the moment is the reassurance that we will continue to
                            follow the development of this project with the most sympathetic
                            interest and that we have every desire to be helpful within feasible
                            limits and under present circumstances.</p>
                        <p>I understand that you will be back in the United States before long and I
                            am looking forward to seeing you.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
